ology, 278, pp. 244-252. , DOI: 10.1016/S0022-1694(03)00155-0; Horton, P., Schaefli, B., Mezghani, A., Hingray, B., Musy, A., Assessment of climate-change impacts on alpine discharge regimes with climate model uncertainty (2006) Hydrological Processes, 20, pp. 2091-2109. , DOI:10.1002/hyp.6197; (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, , Houghton JT, Ding Y, Griggs DJ, Noguer M, van der Linden PJ, Xiaosu D eds, Cambridge University Press; New York; Jasper, K., Calanca, P., Gyalistras, D., Fuhrer, J., Differential impacts of climate change on the hydrology of two alpine river basins (2004) Climate Research, 26, pp. 113-129; Kling, H., Fürst, J., Nachtnebel, H.P., Seasonal, spatially distributed modelling of accumulation and melting of snow for computing runoff in a long-term, large-basin water balance model (2006) Hydrological Processes, 20, pp. 2141-2156. , DOI: 10.1002/hyp.6203; Knowles, N., Dettinger, M.D., Cayan, D.R., Trends in snowfall versus rainfall in the western United States (2006) Journal of Climate, 19, pp. 4545-4559; Komatsu, H., Kume, T., Otsuki, K., Contemporary role of catchment water balance data for forest evaporation research (2007) Journal of the Japanese Forest Society, 89, pp. 346-359. , in Japanese with English summary; Kondo, J., Nakajima, T., Watanabe, T., A study of forest evapotranspiration restraint due to the soil water content (1994) Journal of Japan Society of Hydrology and Water Resources, 7, pp. 402-410. , in Japanese with English summary; Kondo, J., Watanabe, T., Nakazono, M., Heat budget evaluation of forest evapotranspiration in Japan (1992) Tenki, 39, pp. 685-695. , in Japanese; Kondo, J., Xu, J.Q., Seasonal variations in heat and water balances for non-vegetated surfaces (1997) Journal of Applied Meteorolgy, 36, pp. 1676-1695; Kondo, J., Yamazawa, H., Measurement of snow surface emissivity (1986) Boundary Layer Meteorology, 34, pp. 415-416; Kumagai, T., Katul, G.G., Porporato, A., Saitoh, T.M., Ohashi, M., Ichie, T., Suzuki, M., Carbon and water cycling in a Bornean tropical rainforest under current and future climate scenarios (2004) Advances in Water Resources, 27, pp. 1135-1150. , DOI: 10.1016/j.advwatres.2004.10.002; Kumagai, T., Katul, G.G., Saitoh, T.M., Sata, Y., Manfroi, O.J., Morooka, T., Ichie, T., Porporato, A., Water cycling in a Bornean tropical rain forest under current and projected precipitation scenarios (2004) Water Resources Research, 40, pp. W01104. , DOI: 10.1029/2003WR002226; Kurashima, E., Seki, M., Kato, T., Mukaida, Y., Proposal and estimation of a simulation method for snowmelt near the ground -a study of bottom snowmelt (1999) Transactions of the Japanese Society of Irrigation, Drainage and Rural Engineering, 201, pp. 33-41. , in Japanese with English summary; Laio, F., Porporato, A., Ridolfi, L., Rodriguez-Iturbe, I., Plants in water-controlled ecosystems: Active role in hydrologic processes and response to water stress, II. Probablistic soil moisture dynamics (2001) Advances in Water Resources, 24, pp. 707-723. , DOI: 10.1016/ S0309-1708 (01)00005-7; Lettenmaier, D.P., Gan, T.W., Hydrologic sensitivities of the Sacramento-San Joaquin river basin, California, to global warming (1990) Water Resources Research, 26, pp. 69-86; Link, T., Marks, D., Distributed simulation of snowcover massand energy-balance in the boreal forest (1999) Hydrological Processes, 13, pp. 2439-2452; Lundberg, A., Halldin, S., Snow interception evaporation. Review of measurement techniques, processes and models (2001) Theoretical and Applied Climatology, 70, pp. 117-133; Lundberg, A., Koivusalo, H., Estimating winter evaporation in boreal forests with operational snow course data (2003) Hydrological Processes, 17, pp. 1479-1493. , DOI: 10.1002/hyp.1179; Lundberg, A., Nakai, Y., Thunehed, H., Halldin, S., Snow accumulation in forests from ground and remote-sensing data (2004) Hydrological Processes, 18, pp. 1941-1955. , DOI: 10.1002/hyp.1459; Climate Change 2001: Impacts, Adaptation,